<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,788]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<bibRefCitation author="Horvath" box="[199,372,151,175]" firstAuthor="Horvath" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="152 - 165" refId="ref60391" refString="Horvath, G. (1895) Hemipteres nouveaux d'Europe et des pays limitrophes. Revue d'Entomologie, 14, 152 - 165." type="journal article" year="1895">Horváth (1895)</bibRefCitation>
described the species under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Horvath, 1895" authorityName="Horvath" authorityYear="1895" box="[802,1245,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviceps">
<emphasis box="[802,1076,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Aphelocheirus breviceps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Horvath" box="[1084,1245,151,175]" firstAuthor="Horvath" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="152 - 165" refId="ref60391" refString="Horvath, G. (1895) Hemipteres nouveaux d'Europe et des pays limitrophes. Revue d'Entomologie, 14, 152 - 165." type="journal article" year="1895">Horváth, 1895</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from neighbouring Georgia (Tbilisi); it was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AT" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[679,815,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[679,815,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. aestivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[856,1069,188,212]" firstAuthor="Kanyukova" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1726 - 1731" refId="ref61805" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (1974) Poluzhestkokrylye semeystva Aphelocheiridae (Heteroptera) fauny SSSR. (Water bugs of the family Aphelocheiridae (Heteroptera) in the fauna of the USSR). Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 53, 1726 - 1731 (in Russian, English summary)." type="journal article" year="1974">Kanyukova (1974)</bibRefCitation>
. The earlier records from Iberian Peninsula belong to two endemic species described rather recently— 
<taxonomicName authority="Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989" authorityName="Nieser &amp; Millan" authorityYear="1989" box="[919,1436,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="murcius">
<emphasis box="[919,1176,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Aphelocheirus murcius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser &amp; Millan" box="[1183,1436,223,247]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref66544" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Millan, A. (1989) Two new species of Aphelocheirus from the Iberian Peninsula (Heteroptera: Naucoridae). Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 49, 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1989">Nieser &amp; Millán, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[159,226,260,284]" name="Spain" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Spain</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989" authorityName="Nieser &amp; Millan" authorityYear="1989" box="[291,726,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[291,459,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. occidentalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser &amp; Millan" box="[468,726,260,284]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref66544" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Millan, A. (1989) Two new species of Aphelocheirus from the Iberian Peninsula (Heteroptera: Naucoridae). Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 49, 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1989">Nieser &amp; Millán, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[742,841,260,284]" name="Portugal" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[854,919,260,284]" name="Spain" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Spain</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser &amp; Millan" box="[943,1199,260,284]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref66544" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Millan, A. (1989) Two new species of Aphelocheirus from the Iberian Peninsula (Heteroptera: Naucoridae). Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 49, 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1989">Nieser &amp; Millán 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carbonell &amp; Millan" firstAuthor="Carbonell" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="429 - 435" refId="ref56149" refString="Carbonell, J. A. &amp; Millan, A. (2010) Aphelocheirus murcius Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989 y Aphelocheirus occidentalis Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989 (Hemiptera: Aphelocheiridae) dos hemipteros acuaticos endemicos de la Peninsula Iberica amenazados. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 46, 429 - 435." type="journal article" year="2010">Carbonell &amp; Millán 2010</bibRefCitation>
, Carbonell 
<emphasis box="[337,385,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2011), The record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AT" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[633,770,296,320]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[633,770,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. aestivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[837,938,296,319]" name="Morocco" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Morocco</collectingCountry>
published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gheit" box="[1093,1236,295,319]" firstAuthor="Gheit" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="241 - 249" refId="ref59284" refString="Gheit, A. (1995) Catalogue des Hemipteres Hydrocorises et Amphibiocorises des provinces nord marocaines (1 re note). Entomologiste (Paris), 51, 241 - 249." type="journal article" year="1995">Gheit (1995)</bibRefCitation>
belongs probably to the endemic species 
<taxonomicName authority="Bergevin, 1925" authorityName="Bergevin" authorityYear="1925" box="[414,706,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotroui">
<emphasis box="[414,523,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. rotroui</emphasis>
Bergevin, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, described from a single macropterous male (cf. Polhemus 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
1995, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carbonell &amp; Millan" box="[221,508,367,391]" firstAuthor="Carbonell" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="429 - 435" refId="ref56149" refString="Carbonell, J. A. &amp; Millan, A. (2010) Aphelocheirus murcius Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989 y Aphelocheirus occidentalis Nieser &amp; Millan, 1989 (Hemiptera: Aphelocheiridae) dos hemipteros acuaticos endemicos de la Peninsula Iberica amenazados. Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 46, 429 - 435." type="journal article" year="2010">Carbonell &amp; Millán 2010</bibRefCitation>
, Carbonell 
<emphasis box="[636,684,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. 2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,788]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,403,428]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">Comment.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hoberlandt" box="[284,504,404,428]" firstAuthor="Hoberlandt" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1948 - 1950" refId="ref60113" refString="Hoberlandt, L. (1952 a) Results of the zoological scientific expedition of the National Museum in Praha to Turkey. 2. Hemiptera-Heteroptera I. The aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera of Turkey. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 26 (352) (1948 - 1950), 1 - 74 + pls. I - XVII." type="journal article" year="1952" yearSuffix="a">Hoberlandt (1952a)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from the locality ‘Zeylan’ (north of 
<collectingRegion box="[1159,1203,404,427]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Van</collectingRegion>
lake, eastern 
<collectingCountry name="Turkey" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
). The single voucher specimen from Zeylan (
<figureCitation box="[710,846,439,463]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–12" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1391,914,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-182@25.[192,1400,914,1882]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 11–12. Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) aestivalis (Fabricius, 1794), female (Zeylan; 8.2 mm): 11—detail of micropterous hemelytron, 12—habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286733/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 11–12</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoberlandt" box="[871,1078,439,463]" firstAuthor="Hoberlandt" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1948 - 1950" refId="ref60113" refString="Hoberlandt, L. (1952 a) Results of the zoological scientific expedition of the National Museum in Praha to Turkey. 2. Hemiptera-Heteroptera I. The aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera of Turkey. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 26 (352) (1948 - 1950), 1 - 74 + pls. I - XVII." type="journal article" year="1952" yearSuffix="a">Hoberlandt 1952a</bibRefCitation>
) is a brachypterous female. Its comparison with material from the 
<collectingCountry box="[547,725,476,500]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
revealed its general similarity, except for the distinctly shallow incision of the postero-lateral margin of the hemelytron (
<figureCitation box="[796,933,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–12" captionStartId="25.[151,264,1899,1922]" captionTargetBox="[192,1391,914,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-182@25.[192,1400,914,1882]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 11–12. Aphelocheirus (Aphelocheirus) aestivalis (Fabricius, 1794), female (Zeylan; 8.2 mm): 11—detail of micropterous hemelytron, 12—habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5286733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5286733/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 11–12</figureCitation>
). We consider this difference as an intraspecific variability; however, examination of the male genitalia and/or DNA sequences is desirable for final confirmation of the species from 
<collectingCountry box="[421,502,583,607]" name="Turkey" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, considering also the recent evidence of additional cryptic 
<taxonomicName box="[1158,1407,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1158,1320,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Aphelocheirus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[257,320,620,644]" name="Spain" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Spain</collectingCountry>
(Carbonell 
<emphasis box="[463,523,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2011). 
<bibRefCitation author="Nieser &amp; Moubayed" box="[618,941,620,644]" firstAuthor="Nieser" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="247 - 252" refId="ref66583" refString="Nieser, N. &amp; Moubayed, Z. (1985) Les Heteropteres aquatiques du Liban. I. Inventaire faunistique. Annales de Limnologie, 21, 247 - 252." type="journal article" year="1985">Nieser &amp; Moubayed (1985)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<taxonomicName authorityName="AT" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1082,1223,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestivalis">
<emphasis box="[1082,1223,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. aestivalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also from 
<collectingRegion box="[1356,1435,620,644]" country="Turkey" name="Mersin" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Mersin</collectingRegion>
(southern 
<collectingCountry box="[265,367,655,679]" name="Turkey" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
); but N. Nieser (pers. comm. 2010) was not able to retrace the source of the information, and admits a possible confusion with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiritshenko" authorityYear="1925" box="[525,654,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Aphelocheiridae" genus="Aphelocheirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolenatii">
<emphasis box="[525,654,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">A. kolenatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,151,788]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,727,752]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">Identification.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[332,543,727,751]" firstAuthor="Kanyukova" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1726 - 1731" refId="ref61805" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (1974) Poluzhestkokrylye semeystva Aphelocheiridae (Heteroptera) fauny SSSR. (Water bugs of the family Aphelocheiridae (Heteroptera) in the fauna of the USSR). Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 53, 1726 - 1731 (in Russian, English summary)." type="journal article" year="1974">Kanyukova (1974</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[561,622,727,751]" firstAuthor="Kanyukova" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref62197" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Vodnye poluzhestkokrylye nasekomye (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. [Aquatic and semiaquatic (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of the fauna of Russia and neighbouring countries]. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, 296 pp (in Russian, English abstract)." type="book" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
). The life cycle and reproduction were recently treated in detail by 
<bibRefCitation author="Papacek &amp; Soldan" box="[151,442,764,788]" firstAuthor="Papacek" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="299 - 318" refId="ref67431" refString="Papacek, M. &amp; Soldan, T. (2008) Structure and development of the reproductive system in Aphelocheirus aestivalis (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Nepomorpha: Aphelocheiridae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 48, 299 - 318." type="journal article" year="2008">Papáček &amp; Soldán (2008)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
